+---
+assignees:
+- claude-code
+position_column: todo
+position_ordinal: e680
+project: spatial-nav
+title: 'Board: h/j/k/l nav between cards across columns (regression-proof with tests)'
+---
+## What
+
+In the board view, h/j/k/l should move focus between cards:
+- `j` / `k` moves within a column (to the card below / above the focused card)
+- `h` / `l` moves between columns (to the nearest card in the column to the left / right)
+- At a column or row edge, nav clamps — doesn't wrap around
+
+Manual testing confirms this mostly works today ("nav works on board and inspector" once the camelCase serde fix landed). But there is ZERO automated test for it — a regression is one bad edit away, as repeatedly demonstrated this session.
+
+### TDD — failing tests (write before any code)
+
+Under `kanban-app/e2e/spatial-nav-board.e2e.ts` (depends on the E2E harness task):
+
+```ts
+describe("board card navigation", () => {
+  it("j moves focus from card(col 1, row 0) to card(col 1, row 1)", async () => {
+    await openBoardFixture(); // 3 columns × 3 cards each
+    await click(cardEl("card-1-1"));
+    await expectFocused("card-1-1");
+    await keyboard("j");
+    await expectFocused("card-1-2");
+  });
+
+  it("l moves focus across columns at the same vertical level", async () => {
+    await click(cardEl("card-1-2"));
+    await keyboard("l");
+    await expectFocused("card-2-2");
+  });
+
+  it("j at the bottom card of a column stays put", async () => {
+    await click(cardEl("card-2-3"));
+    await keyboard("j");
+    await expectFocused("card-2-3"); // clamped
+  });
+
+  it("h at the leftmost column does NOT wrap", async () => {
+    await click(cardEl("card-1-2"));
+    await keyboard("h");
+    // either stays on card-1-2 (hard clamp) or moves to LeftNav (boundary crossing).
+    // DO NOT wrap to the rightmost column.
+    const focused = await getFocusedMoniker();
+    expect(focused).not.toMatch(/^task:card-3-/);
+  });
+});
+```
+
+All tests must run against the kanban-app E2E harness (tauri-driver + `--only` fixture). Write them to fail first — today there is no such test, so they're "failing by absence" at the very least.
+
+### Likely state
+
+Board nav probably works already; the tests codify the contract. If they pass on first run without code changes, great — add a short comment in the test file saying "codified existing behavior". If they fail, fix.
+
+### Subtasks
+
+- [ ] Extend `kanban-app/src/test_support.rs` with a `write_board_fixture_3x3` helper (3 columns × 3 cards)
+- [ ] Write the 4 failing E2E tests above
+- [ ] Run tests; if all pass, great — lock them in
+- [ ] If any fail, fix minimum required; do not alter unrelated code
+- [ ] No regression in grid / inspector nav
+
+### Acceptance
+
+- [ ] All 4 E2E tests pass reliably (3 consecutive green runs)
+- [ ] `spatial-nav-board.e2e.ts` runs as part of `npm run e2e`
\ No newline at end of file

